function hrCi = cIm2hrCi(cIm)% CIM2HRCI Transforms a uint8 color image (cIm) into a 2D high-res %	(24 bits) classification image (hrCi).%		E.g.,	im = rand(256,256,3);%				cIm = uint8((256 - 1) * im);%				hrCi = cIm2hrCi(cIm);%% See also DEMOSTAT4CI, HRCI2CIM%% The Stat4Ci toolbox is free (http://mapageweb.umontreal.ca/gosselif/random-field.html); if you % use it in your research, please, cite us:% 	Chauvin, A., Worsley, K. J., Schyns, P. G., Arguin, M., & Gosselin, F. (2005). Accurate % 	statistical tests for smooth classification images. Journal of Vision, 5(9), 659-667, % 	http://journalofvision.org/5/9/1/, doi:10.1167/5.9.1.% % Alan Chauvin & Frédéric Gosselin (frederic.gosselin@umontreal.ca), 20/08/2004	cIm = double(cIm);hrCi = cIm(:,:,1) * 256^2 + cIm(:,:,2) * 256 + cIm(:,:,3);